result.title: 2009 Defra MB0102 2B Distribution of Mobile Species quarter rectangle resolution layer
result.name: 2009-defra-mb0102-2b-distribution-of-mobile-species-quarter-rectangle-resolution-layer
result.notes: This layer contains relative abundance information for 12 of the 40 highly mobile species by gear type, Portuguese high headline and beam trawl, at quarter ICES rectangle resolution (0.5 x 0.25 degrees). The data have been obtained from a number of fisheries independent research surveys carried out by England and Wales, Northern Ireland and Scotland.

extras.value: ["Full resolution GIS layer only for viewing by MB0102 partners with publicly available layers available at 10km resolution."]

Full resolution data layer for use only within the MB0102 contract. Permission required from data originators for use in any other context, or by non MB0102 partners. 10km resolution data layer freely available under Open Government Licence.
Centre for Environment, Fisheries and Aquaculture Science, Lowestoft Laboratory (originator); Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs (DEFRA) (custodian)
